		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29140543">I really enjoyed the silly, light-hearted style it had going for the first few episodes. The music is just lovely and Hajime is quite the same. Somewhere in the middle it descended into melodrama and started to focus on its trite story and I sort of lost interest. It should have been this silly, dumb thing for the full duration, because <em>that's</em> what made the first two or three episodes work.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://img541.imageshack.us/img541/6581/v46o.png" /><!--center--></div></div></td>
