		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29314173">Pretty much what Veronin said. I feel I would've enjoyed the work more had it continued on its classic Gatchaman route, where it's bad guys, Gatchaman fights, and slick animation + sound. It's admirable that it tried to tackle social media as a tool for effective organization. However, Gatchaman as well as the majority of works that attempt this—usually to flatter 2ch—rarely delve anymore into the idea that simple collective willingness usurps all evil. Somehow a flat corporate structure is what distinguishes 2ch's greatness from conventional government.<br />
<br />
Certainly the work's meritable aspects lie primarily in its artwork: character designs, colors, city landscapes, Gatchaman, etc. The characters are cool too. Well, maybe not Hajime. :)</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
