		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29375739">I didn't like it to be honest. I found the characters too annyoing (mostly Hajime and the panda thing). It did look nice except for the CGI Gatchaman models. This is actually one of my main grudges. Immersion is rather subjective and depends on the watcher, but usually I can get immersed when watching anime pretty well. The CGI breaks that and I spend half the time thinking about how much I hate that CGI and how out of place it looks. The story became really bizarre at some point but I couldn't relate to either good or bad side, since their motivations and personalities were so... unreal.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
