		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message29399953"><!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>nil- said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br>It's admirable that it tried to tackle social media as a tool for effective organization. <br />
<!--quote--></div><br />
<br />
I felt like if they capitalized on this and executed it better, this could have improved the story dramatically.<br />
<br />
I remember first hearing about a similar concept in Jane McGonigal's book "Reality is Broken." The example she used was something along the lines of (its been a few years since I've read this book, I hope I'm recalling this correctly) people being able to find out through a social media like app on their phones who needed help and where they were. For example, someone is at work exhausted and needs Starbucks coffee to get going, but they're so wrapped up in work that they can't get it. A total stranger would be able to see that they needed coffee on this app and would buy it for them and even bring it to them. This could also be used in much more serious situations. <br />
<br />
So when I saw them doing something similar in Gatchaman Crowds I was excited. I loved that this system was used by people to help complete strangers. And I loved that it was like a game, where you help someone out and even get EXP points and level up. <br />
<br />
Buuut, the story became a bit of a mess at the end. Not only that but the characters were hardly fleshed out. The only one who had an interesting enough personality to me was Hajime. Unfortunately, throughout the show I alternated between wanting to pinch her cheeks and wanting to slap her. I want to know what kind of drugs she was on and where I can get some...<br />
<br />
Overall I think it was a fun little light-hearted show with amazing art. But it didn't capitalize on any of its great concepts. It just kinda threw stuff together and rolled with it, which prevented the anime from being truly great, in my opinion.<br />
<br />
Despite my grievances, I'm excited to see what they do with the show in the second season.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://imageshack.us/a/img547/8390/xw.png" /><!--center--></div><br />
</div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
